# Force textual diffs for source files.
#
# git auto-detects a file as "binary" (and hides its diff) if it finds a NUL
# byte in the first 8 KB of the blob. A stray control byte accidentally embedded
# in a string literal can therefore make a perfectly ordinary source file
# un-reviewable in diffs. Setting the `diff` attribute tells git to always treat
# these paths as text — without touching line-ending normalization (no `text`
# attribute), so nothing gets re-normalized.
*.ts   diff
*.tsx  diff
*.js   diff
*.jsx  diff
*.json diff
*.css  diff
